setPositiveNegative() - Methode in Klasse Datastructures.Clauses.Clause
determines for an ATLEAST- or OR-clause the clause's structure: If the limit is too large: CONTRADICTORY
If the limit is 0: TAUTOLOGY,
If the limit is the clause's size then the connective is changed to AND, and the limit to -1
otherwise if the clause has only positive literals (POSITIVE) or only negative literals (NEGATIVE) or mixed signs (MIXED)

Symboltable - Klasse in Datastructures
Created by ohlbach on 25.08.2018.
The symboltable maps predicate names to integers.
In source files with clauses one may use symbolic names for predicates, but internally a predicate is a positive integer and a literal is a positive or negative integer.
The class guarantees injectivity of the mapping.
Symboltable(int) - Konstruktor für Klasse Datastructures.Symboltable
Creates a new symboltable for a given number of predicates.
